content: On weekends, young people come out like flea markets, selling a variety of cute things such as food, crafts, etc. It's fun. There are many cafes and restaurants in the building, so it's a good idea to visit Seoul Forest!
It was crowded even on Monday evening with many stalls selling similar things.
Plenty of yummie Street Foods at Myeongdong Night Market.
the food selection has gotten smaller over the years, and is quite costly, but still a good go to spot if it's your first time to seoul and want to experience some night life!
